<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-439-950  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 439 950.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  July 17 1989 n547 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Randamp;D self-scrutiny. (Uncommon Market) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woolnough, Roger.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Research and development activities in Europe differ from countryto country and from company to company.andP;  West Germany is theleader in Randamp;D spending, with half of the survey respondentsspending between 5.1 percent and 10 percent of revenue on Randamp;D.andO;Companies in Britain, France and the Netherlands typically spendless than five percent on Randamp;D.andP;  Industry observers believe thatEurope's competitive problems have more to do with the transfer oftechnology to the production line than with Randamp;D.andP;  Only 46 percentof the British respondents and 38 percent of the Frenchrespondents believe that manufacturing technologies have giventhem a competitive edge.andP;  West German companies rated themselvesvery high in regard to the implementation of computer-aidedengineering capabilities, automation and robotics.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentEuropeForeign CompetitionSurveyCritique.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>